42:09.736 --> 42:11.647
Oh, my God.

42:14.324 --> 42:18.192
I am so, so sorry
I put you in the middle of all this.

42:18.995 --> 42:21.452
I know you're probably
still furious with me...

42:22.666 --> 42:24.406
...but please...

42:25.168 --> 42:28.001
...please know how grateful I am.

42:29.881 --> 42:31.496
I know you are.

42:34.177 --> 42:37.010
Can I at least offer you
something to drink?

42:38.348 --> 42:40.134
Bar is open.

42:40.934 --> 42:44.176
And it's fruity.

42:48.692 --> 42:50.353
I'm gonna need more than one.

42:51.862 --> 42:53.272
PATRICK:
What do you think?

42:53.488 --> 42:56.070
TERRY:
It's the last structure left on the property.

42:59.327 --> 43:01.534
PATRICK:
I think Eller took off.

43:16.344 --> 43:18.426
-Give me a hand.
-Yup.

43:20.932 --> 43:22.342
Whoa.

43:29.691 --> 43:30.771
Sergeant.

43:45.332 --> 43:49.826
Jesus Christ.
Bellefleur, you need to see this.

43:58.595 --> 44:00.756
TERRY:
Holy God almighty.

44:00.972 --> 44:02.473
PATRICK:
I knew it.

44:03.308 --> 44:05.594
I knew that motherfucker was sick.

44:05.811 --> 44:07.017
[GUN COCKS]

44:07.187 --> 44:08.677
And armed.

44:12.818 --> 44:14.604
Sorry I'm late.

44:18.698 --> 44:20.234
Guys?

44:21.827 --> 44:23.442
Suzanne?

44:23.870 --> 44:25.030
Emory?

44:25.205 --> 44:27.036
[SAM GASPS]

44:28.458 --> 44:29.538
Oh, God.

44:31.962 --> 44:34.169
[KNOCKING ON COFFIN]

44:34.339 --> 44:36.421
Come on. It's way past sundown.

44:36.591 --> 44:38.752
No vampire of mine sleeps all night.

44:39.344 --> 44:41.960
What the hell happened to you?

44:42.472 --> 44:43.848
And who's she?

44:44.015 --> 44:45.721
Nothing. And Melanie.

44:45.892 --> 44:48.508
She's here because someone needs to feed.

44:49.688 --> 44:53.180
Seriously, three days old
and she has an eating disorder. Why me?

44:53.775 --> 44:55.106
Get the fuck away.

44:55.277 --> 44:58.110
Don't you understand
I was human three days ago?

44:58.280 --> 45:01.488
I can't look at another person
like she's dinner.

45:02.158 --> 45:05.616
-Listen, you seem--
MELANIE: Delicious?

45:06.037 --> 45:09.871
l was gonna say nice, but okay. Um-- Uh--

45:10.083 --> 45:13.325
-lt's not you. | just don't know--
-Oh, no, it's fine.

45:13.503 --> 45:15.334
I don't mind.

45:19.718 --> 45:22.334
-|-- I can't do it.
-You have to.

45:22.512 --> 45:24.093
-No.No.
-Do it.

45:24.264 --> 45:26.630
-|'|| say it. Do it or I'll say it.
-Please don't.

45:26.808 --> 45:29.550
-No. Please, no.
-As your maker, I command you.

45:29.728 --> 45:32.014
-Bite her.
MELANIE: Unh!

45:33.398 --> 45:35.514
Slow down. You'll kill her.

45:35.692 --> 45:39.435
Take her to the precipice of dead,
then hold her there.

45:39.613 --> 45:44.607
Blood drained of oxygen is pure and thick.

45:44.784 --> 45:46.945
There now.

45:47.120 --> 45:49.736
You don't even have to try.

45:49.915 --> 45:53.453
Let it flow to you. Her heart's pulsing.

45:53.627 --> 45:58.212
-Her life, it's yours. Drink.
-Ah....

45:59.132 --> 46:00.963
[MELANIE GRUNTING]

46:01.509 --> 46:05.343
This is who you are now.
The top of the chain.

46:05.513 --> 46:09.677
No human can hurt you any longer.

46:09.851 --> 46:12.763
They're yours to savor.

46:30.080 --> 46:32.867
[SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

46:39.005 --> 46:43.089
At least that's what the scientists call it.
A bit clumsy for my taste.

46:43.259 --> 46:46.001
I prefer the colloquial.

46:48.098 --> 46:50.339
-The Judas Tree.
-Ah.

46:50.517 --> 46:55.352
There. Now, that tells us everything,
doesn't it?

46:56.398 --> 47:01.563
And thus it was from this bough
that Judas lscariot hanged himself.

47:01.736 --> 47:05.149
The tip, melted down
from his 30 pieces of silver...

47:05.323 --> 47:08.736
...the price paid for his betrayal.

47:08.910 --> 47:12.243
That is, if you believe in that sort of thing.

47:12.831 --> 47:14.571
It's what the book tells us.

47:14.749 --> 47:17.991
Yes, but really, who is to say?

47:18.169 --> 47:21.457
Any shard of wood will do the job.

47:21.631 --> 47:24.794
But if you take the book literally...

47:25.010 --> 47:28.502
...then, yes, here it is.

47:30.598 --> 47:32.930
The holy of the holies.

47:34.477 --> 47:38.811
We all have matters to attend to.
May | motion to adjourn?

47:38.982 --> 47:42.019
No, no, I can't do that.
I'm having your quarters searched.

47:43.278 --> 47:47.112
Guardian, it is not possible. We are all loyal.

47:47.282 --> 47:50.149
And we all know that there are extremists...

47:50.326 --> 47:53.614
...who still refuse to recognize
the wisdom of mainstreaming.

47:53.788 --> 47:57.827
If one chancellor can be swayed
from the path, then why not two?

48:22.734 --> 48:24.099
Is it true?

48:31.993 --> 48:35.281
It is as Nora said. There is another traitor.

48:41.503 --> 48:42.913
Treachery.

48:47.842 --> 48:50.254
Sedition under this roof.

48:56.142 --> 49:00.636
Chancellor Drew, can you explain
why this in your possession?

49:02.148 --> 49:03.433
[WOMAN SCREAMS ON COMPUTER]

49:03.608 --> 49:06.315
ALEXANDER [ON COMPUTER]:
Die, human. You are food to us.

49:06.486 --> 49:09.694
[WOMAN SCREAMING
AND ALEXANDER GRUNTING]

49:12.534 --> 49:16.322
Guardian, I apologize.
It's a stupid memento.

49:16.496 --> 49:19.078
Who here hasn't fed on a human
at some point?

49:19.249 --> 49:22.161
If there are those of us who do,
we certainly don't tape it...

49:22.335 --> 49:25.452
...let alone send it out to Misrata...

49:25.630 --> 49:28.713
...Damascus, St. Petersburg.

49:28.883 --> 49:33.877
Sent to known enemies of the Authority
with the encrypted message:

49:34.848 --> 49:37.009
"In sympathy...

49:38.059 --> 49:39.560
...and solidarity."

49:43.690 --> 49:45.146
I can explain.

49:45.316 --> 49:48.683
l was infiltrating them,
gaining their trust.

49:49.237 --> 49:50.568
ALEXANDER:
Aah!

49:55.577 --> 50:00.287
Alert your constituents.
There will be no more rebellions.

50:02.041 --> 50:06.455
No further opposition to ourjust cause.

50:06.963 --> 50:09.875
You will...

50:11.843 --> 50:13.629
...fall in line.

50:16.514 --> 50:18.596
Am I understood?

50:30.111 --> 50:31.851
Bless the blood.

50:32.363 --> 50:34.479
[ALL SPEAK IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

50:35.867 --> 50:38.324
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

50:41.998 --> 50:44.205
SOOKIE:
This was a Tara special.

50:44.375 --> 50:47.412
She made it as a joke,
but people kept ordering it.

50:47.587 --> 50:50.624
Triple sec, Amaretto, Bailey's.

50:50.798 --> 50:52.663
-She called it Orange Marzipan.
-No.

50:52.842 --> 50:54.423
I'm nowhere near drunk enough.

50:54.594 --> 50:58.257
That's why you have to have one.
The drunker you are, the less you care.

51:04.938 --> 51:07.725
-That is unbelievably fucking nasty.
-Heh, heh.

51:07.982 --> 51:09.973
[LAUGHS]

51:10.777 --> 51:12.642
How often you do this?

51:13.112 --> 51:14.693
Not enough. Heh, heh.

51:14.906 --> 51:15.986
[CHUCKLES]

51:16.157 --> 51:19.945
| feel good for the first time
in who knows?

51:21.287 --> 51:23.198
I think the whole world hates me...

51:23.373 --> 51:27.116
...but they can just go bite me,
those who haven't already.

51:29.170 --> 51:32.037
I killed your ex-girlfriend,
and you're still speaking to me.

51:32.215 --> 51:34.251
Well, I'm mainly here for the drinks.

51:34.467 --> 51:37.834
-Then finish your Orange Marzipan.
-I don't want any. It's disgusting.

51:38.012 --> 51:40.219
-But I made it for you.
-I don't give a fuck.

51:40.390 --> 51:43.097
-Come on. You'll do anything for me.
-Yeah? Well, not that.

51:43.268 --> 51:45.884
-Yes, you will. You're in love with me.
-Screw you.

51:46.729 --> 51:48.139
That's what you think, huh?

52:01.577 --> 52:03.192
ERIC:
Awkward time for a drop-in, Bill.

52:04.580 --> 52:08.038
Jessica mentioned Sookie had been having
a rough go of it.

52:08.209 --> 52:11.701
ERIC:
Hm. She seems to be recovering nicely.

52:13.756 --> 52:17.374
-Can we go back to looking for Russell now?
-We are looking for Russell.

52:17.552 --> 52:19.668
Clearly without any success.

52:20.471 --> 52:22.257
Sookie could be useful.

52:23.224 --> 52:26.011
I don't think she wants anything
to do with us again.

52:26.394 --> 52:29.227
I don't think we give her the choice.

52:31.566 --> 52:34.273
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS
AND PEOPLE CHATTERING]

52:34.861 --> 52:37.227
[JASON MOANING]

52:45.079 --> 52:47.411
LEDA:
You're thinking of someone else.

52:48.249 --> 52:50.160
A vampire?

52:50.335 --> 52:52.576
Wait. Did you just read--?

52:56.424 --> 52:58.039
What is this place?

52:58.217 --> 52:59.957
HADLEY:
Jason?

53:01.137 --> 53:02.718
Hadley?

53:03.264 --> 53:05.971
-Oh, my God.
HADLEY: Ha, ha.

53:07.226 --> 53:08.841
Thank goodness.

53:09.020 --> 53:12.353
Leda, this is my cousin l was
telling you about. Well, one of them. Ha, ha.

53:12.523 --> 53:14.559
Wait, wait, wait. When did you get back?

53:14.734 --> 53:17.020
-Does Sookie know you're here?
-Sookie?

53:17.195 --> 53:19.060
-Yeah.
-She's alive?

53:19.781 --> 53:21.567
Yeah, of course she's alive.

53:21.741 --> 53:24.027
Oh, my God.
I thought after she disappeared...

53:24.202 --> 53:27.990
-Jason, we gotta go get her.
-Wait. Hadley, do you work here?

53:28.206 --> 53:31.118
Don't worry. I don't touch anybody.
I could probably get you a job.

53:31.292 --> 53:32.953
-Do you dance?
-Yeah.

53:33.127 --> 53:36.585
-But I don't need a job.
-Aren't you a refugee?

53:36.756 --> 53:38.838
A refugee? From what?

53:39.008 --> 53:42.546
The vampires.
That's why I brought my son.

53:43.513 --> 53:46.880
What, is this some kind of—-?
Some kind of fairy safe house?

53:47.058 --> 53:49.720
Vampires will drain anyone
with a drop of fairy blood...

53:49.894 --> 53:52.306
...if they don't stay together.
We gotta get Sookie.

53:52.480 --> 53:56.769
The last time Sookie got mixed up with
the fairies, things didn't turn out too good.

53:56.943 --> 54:00.731
-She might be better off with the vampires.
-No, no. She can't be around vampires.

54:00.905 --> 54:02.736
They're gonna turn on her. I know it.

54:02.907 --> 54:05.364
They will kill her,
just like they did your parents.

54:06.953 --> 54:08.568
-What?
LEDA: Hadley.

54:10.456 --> 54:12.242
No. My parents were killed in a flood.

54:13.668 --> 54:15.158
Weren't they?

54:19.632 --> 54:22.169
-Hadley, go now.
JASON: Weren't they?

54:22.343 --> 54:23.958
-Look, I said too much.
-Calm down.

54:24.137 --> 54:26.253
HADLEY: You gotta get Sookie.
-Wait. Excuse me.

54:30.143 --> 54:32.509
Hadley. Where are you going?

54:33.354 --> 54:36.016
BOUNCER: Calm down, sir.
-Take it easy. That's my cousin.

54:36.190 --> 54:38.476
-Get your fucking hands off me!
ANDY: Whoa, whoa, whoa.

54:38.651 --> 54:40.357
-What's the matter?
-Hadley.

54:40.528 --> 54:42.814
Get your hands off him. Back off.

54:43.781 --> 54:46.693
-l'm the sheriff. You don't wanna do this.
-Hadley!

54:50.872 --> 54:52.157
Stackhouse.

54:53.416 --> 54:55.372
[JASON SCREAMS]
